[No author name available],"Environmental effects of ozone depletion and its interactions with climate change: Progress report, 2009",2010,"Photochemical and Photobiological Sciences","9","3",,"275","294",,,10.1039/b923342n,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77949408681&partnerID=40&md5=9467cadc45c2235ab20cf1bf385902c8",,"","The parties to the Montreal Protocol are informed by three panels of experts. One of these is the Environmental Effects Assessment Panel (EEAP), which deals with UV radiation and its effects on human health, animals, plants, biogeochemistry, air quality and materials. Since 2000, the analyses and interpretation of these effects have included interactions between UV radiation and global climate change. When considering the effects of climate change, it has become clear that processes resulting in changes in stratospheric ozone are more complex than believed previously. As a result of this, human health and environmental problems will likely be longer-lasting and more regionally variable. Like the other panels, the EEAP produces a detailed report every four years; the most recent was that for 2006 (Photochem. Photobiol. Sci., 2007, 6, 201-332). In the years in between, the EEAP produces a less detailed and shorter progress report, as is the case for this present one for 2009. A full quadrennial report will follow for 2010. © 2010 The Royal Society of Chemistry and Owner Societies.",,"ozone; air; animal; climate change; ecosystem; environment; human; program development; review; ultraviolet radiation; Air; Animals; Climate Change; Ecosystem; Environment; Humans; Ozone; Program Development; Ultraviolet Rays; Animalia",,"ozone, 10028-15-6; Ozone, 10028-15-6",,,,"Hicke, J.A., Slusser, J., Lantz, K., Pascual, F.G., Trends and interannual variability in surface UVB radiation over 8 to 11 years observed across the United States (2008) J. Geophys. Res., 113, p. 21302; Borkowski, J.L., Modelling of UV radiation variations at different time scales (2008) Ann. Geophys., 26, pp. 441-446; Herman, J., Global increase in UV irradiance during the past 30 years (1979 to 2008) estimated from satellite data (2009) J. Geophys. Res., , 10.1029/2009JD012219; Kumari, B.P., Londhe, A.L., Daniel, S., Jadhav, D.B., Observational evidence of solar dimming: Offsetting surface warming over India (2007) Geophys. Res. Lett., 34, p. 21810; Alpert, P., Kishcha, P., Quantification of the effect of urbanization on solar dimming (2008) Geophys. Res. Lett., 35, p. 08801; Zerefos, C., Eleftheratos, K., Meleti, C., Kazadtzis, S., Romanou, A., Ichoku, C., Tselioudis, G., Bais, A., Solar dimming and brightening over Thessaloniki, Greece, and Beijing, China (2009) Tellus, Ser. B, 61, pp. 657-665; Ohvril, H., Teral, H., Neiman, L., Kannel, M., Uustare, M., Tee, M., Russak, V., Laulainen, N., Global dimming and brightening versus atmospheric column transparency, Europe, 1906-2007 (2009) J. Geophys. Res., 114, pp. 00D12; Liley, J.B., New Zealand dimming and brightening (2009) J. Geophys. Res., 114, pp. 00D10; Wild, M., Global dimming and brightening: A review (2009) J. Geophys. Res., 114, pp. 00D16; Tanskanen, A., Lindfors, A., Maatta, A., Krotkov, N., Herman, J., Kaurola, J., Koskela, T., Tamminen, J., Validation of the daily erythemal UV doses from ozone monitoring instrument with ground-based UV measurement data (2007) J. Geophys. Res., 112, pp. 24S44; Kazadzis, S., Bais, A., Arola, A., Krotkov, N., Kouremeti, N., Meleti, C., Ozone Monitoring Instrument spectral UV irradiance products: Comparison with ground based measurements at an urban environment (2009) Atmos. Chem. Phys., 9, pp. 585-594; McKenzie, R.L., Weinreis, C., Johnston, P.V., Liley, B., Shiona, H., Kotkamp, M., Smale, D., Kondo, Y., Effects of urban pollution on UV spectral irradiances (2008) Atmos. Chem. Phys., 8, pp. 5683-5697; Panicker, A.S., Pandithurai, G., Takamura, T., Pinker, R.T., Aerosol effects in the UV-B spectral region over Pune, an urban site in India (200